<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1437] DS 1.1 signatures for activators and bind methods only available for declaration with new namespace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1437</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The draft compendium specification (dated 2009/03/10) states:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    The additional signatures and additional accessibility for the activate,&lt;br/&gt;
    deactivate, bind and unbind methods can cause problems for components&lt;br/&gt;
    written to version 1.0 of this specification. The behaviour in this&lt;br/&gt;
    specification only applies to component descriptions using the v1.1.0&lt;br/&gt;
    name space.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently the new method signatures are checked and accepted regardless of the namespace version of the component declaration. If a component is declared with a 1.0 namespace declaration, only the original signatures must be accepted, which are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;methods must be protected or public&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;bind methods take ServiceReference or service object&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;activator methods take ComponentContext&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
